<br>
Besides getting together with old and new friends in the open raid community, the highlight was the battle with Lord Nagafen.  With great skill and precision the raid force took out Nagafen with ONLY TWO PLAYERS DEAD AT THE END OF THE FIGHT (Voksor (MA) and Korhil (Paladin)).  Truly excellent buffing, main tanking, LoH rotation, and support from everyone involved.   <br>
<br>
Though that part of the raid was memorable, the loot was a bit less so; let's just say that many an epic seeker was left sitting in Nagafen's Lair with no epic pieces to roll on.  <br>
<br>
Here's what was looted and rolled on (off the top of my head, correct me if I am wrong):<br>
<br>
1.  Gold Kashigatana -- Emosewa<br>
<br>
2.  Bladestopper -- Pien<br>
<br>
3.  Bladestopper -- Knor <br>
<br>
4.  Hammer -- Balthag<br>
<br>
5.  Razing Blade -- Cyraen (won this with a roll of 28!)<br>
<br>
6.  Mithril Mask -- Corinna (aka Group 7)<br>
<br>
7.  Blackened Mithril Boots -- Borblefoot<br>
<br>
8.  Mithril Torque -- Medite (I Try Not to Win But Sometimes   Lightning Strikes).<br>
<br>
9.  Gloves of Fiery Might -- Shabba (Thanks For Reminding Me)<br>
<br>
I wish to thank all those who came out to make this event a success and I look forward to putting on other open Nagafen Raids in the future.<br>
<br>
Thanks again to all who came out and kicked some dragon butt,<br>
<br>
Medite Marconus<br>
